<text id="04-procedure" title="uv as the Python Lockfile Floor Procedure" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="800" depth="essential">
  <summary>5-step procedure to apply the uv-lockfile-floor methodology end-to-end. Decision-gates surface stops when inputs do not pass.</summary>

  <section title="Procedure">

    <step n="1" name="install-uv">
      <input>Developer machine + CI image</input>
      <action>Install `uv` (≥ 0.6) everywhere; verify `uv --version`.</action>
      <output>uv reachable.</output>
    </step>
    <step n="2" name="migrate-pyproject">
      <input>Existing pyproject + lock</input>
      <action>Convert dependencies into `[project.dependencies]` / `[tool.uv]`; run `uv lock`.</action>
      <output>templates/pyproject.toml + uv.lock.</output>
    </step>
    <step n="3" name="delete-legacy-locks">
      <input>Repo scan</input>
      <action>Remove `poetry.lock`, `requirements*.txt`, `Pipfile.lock` in the same PR.</action>
      <output>Single-lock invariant.</output>
    </step>
    <step n="4" name="pin-python">
      <input>Team policy</input>
      <action>Set `requires-python = &apos;&gt;=X.Y,&lt;X.(Y+1)&apos;` and `python-version` in `.python-version`.</action>
      <output>Python version pinned.</output>
    </step>
    <step n="5" name="add-agents-md-snippet">
      <input>AGENTS.md</input>
      <action>Insert `templates/agents-md-snippet.md` content into the project&apos;s AGENTS.md.</action>
      <output>Snippet committed.</output>
    </step>

  </section>
</text>
